## Overview

This document establishes frontend development standards for the LTI React application. All frontend code must follow these standards without exception to ensure consistency, maintainability, and accessibility.

**Key principles**:
- **English only**: All code, comments, and user-facing text must be in English
- **Functional components + hooks**: Modern React patterns only; no class components
- **TypeScript strict mode**: Full type safety; no `any` types
- **Accessibility first**: WCAG 2.1 AA compliance for all interactive components
- **Composable components**: Small, focused, single-responsibility components
- **Service-based API**: Centralized HTTP communication in service layer
- **>80% test coverage**: Comprehensive testing of components and services

