## React Component Standards

### Functional Components Only

**All components must be functional components using React hooks**. No class components ever.

```typescript
// Good: Functional component with hooks
export const CandidateForm: React.FC<CandidateFormProps> = ({ onSubmit }) => {
    const [formData, setFormData] = useState<CandidateFormData>(initialData);
    
    const handleChange = (field: keyof CandidateFormData, value: string) => {
        setFormData(prev => ({ ...prev, [field]: value }));
    };
    
    return (
        <Form onSubmit={handleSubmit}>
            {/* form fields */}
        </Form>
    );
};

// Bad: Class component
class CandidateForm extends React.Component {
    state = { formData: initialData };
    // ...
}
```

### Component File Organization

Each component should have these files:

```
ComponentName/
├── ComponentName.tsx           # Component implementation
├── ComponentName.module.css    # Component-scoped styles (CSS Modules)
├── ComponentName.test.tsx      # Component tests
└── types.ts                    # TypeScript types (if complex)
```

**Alternative for simple components**: Single file with inline styles or CSS.

### Props Interface Pattern

Always define explicit TypeScript interfaces for component props:

```typescript
// Good: Clear, explicit props interface
interface CandidateFormProps {
    initialData?: Candidate;
    onSubmit: (data: CandidateFormData) => Promise<void>;
    isLoading?: boolean;
}

export const CandidateForm: React.FC<CandidateFormProps> = ({
    initialData,
    onSubmit,
    isLoading = false
}) => {
    // implementation
};

// Bad: Using `any`
export const CandidateForm = (props: any) => { /* ... */ };

// Bad: No types
export const CandidateForm = ({ initialData, onSubmit, isLoading }) => { /* ... */ };
```

### Component Naming

```typescript
// Good: Descriptive PascalCase names
export const AddCandidateForm = () => { /* ... */ };
export const CandidateCard = () => { /* ... */ };
export const LoadingSpinner = () => { /* ... */ };

// Bad: Generic names
export const Form = () => { /* ... */ };
export const Card = () => { /* ... */ };
export const Spinner = () => { /* ... */ };
```

